# VM in-flight monitor (adaptive)

**Canon script:** `scripts/ppe_in_flight_monitor.py` · **Entry:** `ppe_in_flight_monitor.cmd`

When `wait_for_vm` or VM phase is `BUILD_IN_FLIGHT` / `FINISH_IN_FLIGHT`: **monitor until clear** — do not end the operator thread on passive wait.

## One pass (agent thread loop)

```bat
ppe_in_flight_monitor.cmd
ppe_in_flight_monitor.cmd --json
```

Repeat when `next_poll_s` elapsed (or sleep in `--daemon`). Report to founder only on **phase change**, **stuck**, or **action_ready**.

## Adaptive cadence (defaults)

| Condition | Next check |
|-----------|------------|
| Mirror stale | ~1m (+ git refresh) |
| Healthy in-flight (<30m) | ~30m |
| Approaching stuck (30–45m) | ~10m |
| Stuck (≥45m) | ~5m + escalate |

## Escalation (≥45m same phase)

One bounded SSH per hour: `ppe_autobuilder.cmd advance` on VM (script runs this when `--no-escalate` not set).

Manual recovery: `@ppe-autobuilder-operator` diagnose · VM `fix_vm_operator.cmd` if advance fails.

## Phase cleared

| Outcome | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `completion_action` = DESKTOP_CONTINUE | Run `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd --no-pause` (or `@ppe-finish-worker`) |
| `done` + no action | Rotate thread; run normal burst path |

Optional: `ppe_in_flight_monitor.cmd --daemon --auto-act` runs completion when clear (opt-in).

## Auto-start (opt-in)

Set `PPE_AUTO_DISPATCH=1` (see `ppe_operator_dispatch.py`). On `wait_for_vm`, `prepare_operator_status` starts detached monitor with `--auto-act`. On `action_ready`, runs `DESKTOP_CONTINUE.cmd --no-pause` once.

Manual: `ppe_in_flight_monitor.cmd --start` / `--stop`

## Do NOT

- Parallel SSH probes or `@ppe-director` while `wait_for_vm`
- Fixed 5m polling regardless of state
- Trust stale SSH cache over fresh `docs/SOP/VM_OPERATOR_PHASE.json`

**State:** `artifacts/control_plane/IN_FLIGHT_MONITOR_STATE.json`
